The paper deals with location privacy in the context of location-based services, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses optimization frameworks and noise functions, which are topics that are commonly studied in the fields of databases (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper considers the notion of geo-indistinguishability, which is a concept that is relevant to the field of social and information networks (cs.SI).
